  "text": "Another approach is to parameterize the ROC curve directly. The most common form is the binormal ROC curve, ROC(t) = Φ {a + bΦ −1 (t)}, for which the partial AUC is given by the same formula above. However, because this approach does not parameterize the distributions of test results, but only the ROC curve that describes the relationship between their distributions, it stipulates far weaker assumptions. Two methods have been proposed for estimating parameters a and b of the binormal ROC curve [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
